key_points: Wisconsin prosecutors request an arrest warrant for Kyle Rittenhouse for not disclosing his new address post bail.
Rittenhouse accused of killing two and wounding one during the Jacob Blake protests in Kenosha, Wisconsin.
Rittenhouse's legal team argues his location is kept secret due to death threats.
Bond was set at $2 million, which was met through fundraising efforts led by Lin Wood and contributions from Mike Lindell and Ricky Schroder.
Rittenhouse pleaded not guilty to charges including two felony counts of homicide and a felony count of attempted homicide.
After arraignment, Rittenhouse seen in a bar with his mother, displaying symbols associated with white supremacy.
Prosecutors request additional bond conditions, including a ban on alcohol and association with white supremacist groups.
Rittenhouse's attorney argues he has never been part of listed supremacist groups and does not object to new bond conditions.
Prosecutors are also seeking a $200,000 increase in Rittenhouse's bond.
Rittenhouse is set to return to court for jury selection on March 29.
spokespersons: John Pierce (Former part of Rittenhouse's defense team)
